    {%- comment -%}
      ✅ CHANGE 4: Removed the forceHeaderActive JS block entirely.
      That script was:
        - Render-blocking (inline <script> in <head> without defer/async)
        - Running on every scroll event
        - Using setTimeouts at 100ms / 500ms / 1000ms (jank-inducing)
        - Fighting the theme's own JS (MutationObserver on top of theme observers)
      The CSS fix above (always showing the logo) achieves the same result without JS.
      If the theme's sticky logic re-hides it, address that in header.liquid instead.
    {%- endcomment -%}

